caption.title: Peridomestic Ae. malayensis in Singapore are orally susceptible to YFV.
caption.p: Dose-response curves are shown for the Ae. malayensis population from Singapore under study and a control Ae. aegypti population. Infection rate is the proportion of blood-fed females testing YFV-positive 10â€“14 days post blood meal. Dissemination rate is the proportion of YFV-infected females with YFV-positive wings/legs or head 14 days post blood meal. The line represents the logistic regression of the data and the shaded area is the 95% confidence interval of the fit. The data shown are combined from two separate experiments.
